He had grown tall of his age, still wanting
some months of sixteen. His features were
pretty yet, and his eye and complexion brighter
than I remembered them, though with merely
temporary lustre borrowed from the salubrious
air and genial sun.

“ Now, who is that ?” asked Mr. Heathcliff,
turning to Cathy. “ Can you tell ?”

“ Your son?” she said, having doubtfully
surveyed, ﬁrst one, and then the other.

